Commentary Text: Kartik Tyagi to Dhoni, out Dhoni Run Out!! 1 run completed. Appeal for a run-out, MS was scampering back for the second. Has he made his ground? It looks tight, this looks OUT. He did slide his bat in, but did he get it past the crease when the bails lit up? No, says the third umpire - OUT, it is. That's a big blow for CSK - could make a difference of at least 10-15 runs. Casual from MS, don't think he thought there was a second there, was casually ambling across for the first and then decides to take the second once Archer fumbled. He's quick to recover and throws it at the right end, MS did push hard, but he was done in by the smallest of margins. Dhoni run out (Jofra Archer/Samson) 28(28) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: Chahar to Uthappa, leg byes, 1 run, a review for leg-before. Dhoni was hesitant but Chahar convinces him. This is a reasonable shout. Length ball swinging away late from middle and off, Uthappa's flick shot is designed for a delivery going straight on. It curves past his outside edge onto the back leg. Would've just clipped the outside of off stump so it stays with the onfield call
